What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Post-Harvest Treatment Market?

Market Analysis and Insights

Post-Harvest Treatment Market

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the post-harvest treatment market will project a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 6.80% during the forecast period of 2022-2029 and is likely to reach USD 2.85 billion in 2029.

Post-harvest treatment is a method of protective & enhancing quality of the product which incorporates fruits, vegetables, and root crops. Basic techniques concerned within the post-harvesting treatment are edible coatings, chemical treatment and temperature management together with heat and irradiation that helps in restoring antioxidants, antimicrobials & permits anti-browning

The high demand for fresh fruits and vegetables all over the globe is the major factor accelerating the growth of the post-harvest treatment market. Furthermore, rising awareness regarding the need for post-harvest losses are expected to increase the demand for post-harvest treatments for fruit and vegetables and growing concern towards for post-harvest treatment among the players are also expected to drive the growth of the post-harvest treatment market. However, stringent government regulations related to quality of food and high price of treatment will restrains the post-harvest treatment market, whereas, lack of efficient infrastructure for post-harvest mechanisms will challenge market growth.

In addition, Innovative post-harvest handling treatments and handling practises will create ample opportunities for the post-harvest treatment market.

